  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Hemi- or total knee arthroplasty.

          -  18 - 70 years of age.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Concurrent diseases that compromises treatment, i.e.hip disease, rheumatoid arthritis,
             migraine).

          -  Bleeding disorders.

          -  Heart disease or use of pacemaker.

          -  Lack of patient cooperation, i.e. psychological disorders, alcoholism, problems with
             language).

          -  Infection.

        Exclusion criteria during intervention:

          -  Infection.

          -  Cicatrice-burst.
      </textblock>
